  "prompt": "What is Tacometer?",
  "response": "A tachometer is an instrument used to measure the rotational speed of a shaft or disk, typically in revolutions per minute (RPM). It is commonly found in vehicles, where it measures the speed of the engine's crankshaft, helping drivers monitor engine performance and maintain optimal operating speeds. Tachometers can also be used in various other applications, such as machinery and industrial equipment, to ensure they are operating within safe and efficient speed ranges. There are several types of tachometers, including mechanical, electronic, and optical, each using different methods to measure and display rotational speed.",
